 and the Denver metro area."}},{"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Home Insurance","description":"Homeowners insurance to protect your property, belongings, and liability in Wheat Ridge and surrounding Colorado communities."}},{"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Life Insurance","description":"Term and whole life insurance solutions to secure your family's financial future."}},{"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Business Insurance","description":"Commercial insurance including general liability, property, and workers compensation for Wheat Ridge businesses."}},{"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Renters Insurance","description":"Affordable renters insurance to protect personal property and provide liability coverage for tenants."}},{"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Condo Insurance","description":"Specialized condo insurance that complements HOA master policies for condo owners in Colorado."}}]},"founder":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jubal Terry","jobTitle":"Farmers Insurance Agent","knowsAbout":["Auto Insurance","Home Insurance","Life Insurance","Business Insurance","Renters Insurance","Condo Insurance"]},"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5.0","reviewCount":"11","bestRating":"5"}}9:T71f,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What insurance products does Jubal Terry offer in Wheat Ridge?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Jubal Terry offers a full range of insurance products through Farmers Insurance including auto insurance, home insurance, life insurance, business insurance, renters insurance, and condo insurance. He also has access to independent markets and specialty carriers for non-standard coverage needs."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Where is Insurance Wheat Ridge located?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Insurance Wheat Ridge is located at 4251 Kipling St, Unit 165, Wheat Ridge, CO 80033. We serve Wheat Ridge, Lakewood, Arvada, Golden, Edgewater, and the greater Denver metro area."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What neighborhoods and areas does Insurance Wheat Ridge serve?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We serve clients throughout Wheat Ridge, Lakewood, Arvada, Golden, Edgewater, and the broader Denver metro area including Jefferson County, Denver County, Larimer County, and Broomfield County."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the office hours for Insurance Wheat Ridge?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our office hours are Monday through Friday, 8:30 AM to 5:00 PM. We are closed on Saturday and Sunday. You can reach us by phone at (303) 464-1911 or by email at jterry1@farmersagent.com."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I get a free insurance quote from Jubal Terry?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Getting a free quote is easy! You can call us directly at (303) 464-1911, visit our office at 4251 Kipling St Unit 165 in Wheat Ridge, or fill out the contact form on our website. Jubal will personally review your needs and provide a customized quote."}}]}0:["MDD_mQPVBu_-RxWkOp-ED",[[["",{"children":["blog",{"children":[["slug","small-business-insurance-101-wheat-ridge","d"],{"children":["__PAGE__?{\"slug\":\"small-business-insurance-101-wheat-ridge\"}",{}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["blog",{"children":[["slug","small-business-insurance-101-wheat-ridge","d"],{"children":["__PAGE__",{},[["$L1",["$","div",null,{"className":"min-h-screen","children":[["$","$L2",null,{}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Article\",\"headline\":\"Small Business Insurance 101: Protecting Your Wheat Ridge Business\",\"description\":\"Running a small business means wearing a lot of hats. Here's a plain-language guide to the coverage that keeps your business — and your livelihood — protected.\",\"image\":\"https://www.insurancewheatridge.com/images/blog-small-business-insurance.png\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-03-01\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Person\",\"name\":\"Jubal Terry\",\"jobTitle\":\"Farmers Insurance Agent\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Insurance Wheat Ridge\"}}"}}],["$","article",null,{"className":"py-12 bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container mx-auto px-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium mb-6","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":16,"height":16,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-arrow-left","aria-hidden":"true","children":[["$","path","1l729n",{"d":"m12 19-7-7 7-7"}],["$","path","x3x0zl",{"d":"M19 12H5"}],"$undefined"]}],"Back to Blog"]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full font-medium text-xs","children":"Business Insurance"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":14,"height":14,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-calendar","aria-hidden":"true","children":[["$","path","1cmpym",{"d":"M8 2v4"}],["$","path","4m81vk",{"d":"M16 2v4"}],["$","rect","1hopcy",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"4","rx":"2"}],["$","path","8toen8",{"d":"M3 10h18"}],"$undefined"]}],"March 1, 2026"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":14,"height":14,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-clock","aria-hidden":"true","children":[["$","path","mmk7yg",{"d":"M12 6v6l4 2"}],["$","circle","1mglay",{"cx":"12","cy":"12","r":"10"}],"$undefined"]}],"6 min read"]}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 leading-tight","children":"Small Business Insurance 101: Protecting Your Wheat Ridge Business"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-8 pb-8 border-b border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center","children":["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":20,"height":20,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-user text-blue-700","aria-hidden":"true","children":[["$","path","975kel",{"d":"M19 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H9a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"}],["$","circle","17ys0d",{"cx":"12","cy":"7","r":"4"}],"$undefined"]}]}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-gray-900","children":"Jubal Terry"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-gray-500","children":"Farmers Insurance Agent | Wheat Ridge, CO"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"relative rounded-2xl overflow-hidden mb-10 aspect-[16/9]","children":["$","$L4",null,{"src":"/images/blog-small-business-insurance.png","alt":"Cartoon of a stressed small business owner surrounded by hazards - humorous insurance illustration","fill":true,"className":"object-cover","priority":true}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-custom","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"If you run a small business in Wheat Ridge or anywhere in the Denver metro area, you've probably thought about insurance at some point — and then immediately moved on to the twelve other things demanding your attention. I get it. Insurance isn't the most exciting part of running a business. But it's one of the most important."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"One lawsuit, one accident, one fire — any of these can put a small business under if the right protection isn't in place. And the reality is, most business owners I talk to are either underinsured or paying for coverage they don't actually need. Let's fix that."}],["$","h2","4",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4","children":"The Core Coverages Every Small Business Should Consider"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Every business is different, but there are a few types of insurance that apply to almost everyone:"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"General Liability Insurance"}]," — This is the foundation. General liability covers claims related to bodily injury, property damage, and personal or advertising injury that arise from your business operations. If a customer slips in your store, if your work accidentally damages a client's property, or if you're accused of making a misleading claim in your advertising, general liability responds."]}],["$","p","10",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"For many small businesses, this is the first policy to put in place — and sometimes the only one required by lease agreements or contracts."}],["$","p","12",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Commercial Property Insurance"}]," — This covers your physical business assets: the building (if you own it), equipment, inventory, furniture, signage, and supplies. If a fire, theft, vandalism, or weather event damages your property, commercial property insurance helps pay for repairs or replacements."]}],["$","p","14",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Even if you operate from a home office, your personal homeowner's policy may not cover business equipment. It's worth asking about."}],["$","p","16",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Business Owner's Policy (BOP)"}]," — A BOP bundles general liability and commercial property insurance into a single policy, usually at a lower cost than buying them separately. For many small businesses — retail shops, restaurants, professional offices, service providers — a BOP is the most cost-effective starting point."]}],["$","p","18",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Workers' Compensation"}]," — If you have employees, Colorado law requires you to carry workers' comp insurance. It covers medical expenses and lost wages for employees who are injured or become ill because of their job. Even if you only have one part-time employee, this coverage is mandatory."]}],["$","p","20",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Professional Liability (Errors & Omissions)"}]," — If your business provides professional services or advice, professional liability insurance protects you from claims of negligence, mistakes, or failure to deliver. This is especially relevant for consultants, accountants, IT professionals, real estate agents, and similar service-based businesses."]}],["$","p","22",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Commercial Auto Insurance"}]," — If you or your employees drive vehicles for business purposes — deliveries, client visits, job sites — your personal auto policy probably doesn't cover those activities. Commercial auto insurance fills that gap and protects your business from liability claims involving company vehicles."]}],["$","h2","24",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4","children":"Common Mistakes I See Business Owners Make"}],["$","p","26",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Assuming their home policy covers their business."}]," If you run a business out of your home, most homeowner's policies provide very limited coverage for business property and zero coverage for business liability. A home-based business endorsement or a separate business policy is usually necessary."]}],["$","p","28",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Skipping liability coverage because they haven't been sued yet."}]," The time to get liability insurance is before you need it. Lawsuits are expensive even when you're in the right. Legal defense costs alone can run into five figures before a case is resolved."]}],["$","p","30",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Not reviewing coverage as the business grows."}]," The policy you set up when you opened your doors two years ago may not fit your business today. New equipment, new employees, new services, and increased revenue all affect your coverage needs. I recommend reviewing your business insurance at least once a year."]}],["$","p","32",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Choosing the cheapest option without understanding what's excluded."}]," Price matters, but so does what you're actually getting. A policy that saves you $500 a year but excludes the one type of claim your business is most likely to face isn't a bargain."]}],["$","h2","34",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4","children":"How Much Does Small Business Insurance Cost?"}],["$","p","36",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"This varies a lot depending on your industry, size, location, and risk profile. But to give you a rough idea:"}],["$","ul","ul-41",{"className":"list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6","children":[["$","li","38",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":["A basic BOP for a low-risk service business might run $500–$1,500 per year"]}],["$","li","39",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":["General liability alone can be as low as $300–$600 per year for small operations"]}],["$","li","40",{"className":"text-gray-700","children":["Workers' comp depends on your payroll and industry classification"]}]]}],["$","p","42",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"The best way to know what you'd pay is to get a quote based on your specific situation. I can usually turn one around in a day or two."}],["$","h2","44",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4","children":"The Bottom Line"}],["$","p","46",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Running a business is hard enough without worrying about what happens if something goes wrong. The right insurance doesn't just protect your assets — it protects the time, energy, and money you've invested in building something that matters to you."}],["$","p","48",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"If you're a business owner in Wheat Ridge, Lakewood, Arvada, or the greater Denver area and you're not sure whether your coverage is where it needs to be, let's talk. I'll take a look at what you have, identify any gaps, and make recommendations based on what actually makes sense for your business."}],["$","p","50",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Want to protect your business?"}]," Call me at [(303) 464-1911](tel:3034641911) or email [info@insurancewheatridge.com](mailto:info@insurancewheatridge.com). Let's make sure you're covered."]}],["$","p","52",{"className":"text-gray-500 italic mt-6","children":"— Jubal Terry, Farmers Insurance Agent | Wheat Ridge, CO"}]]}]]}]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-12 bg-gray-50","children":["$","div",null,{"className":